-- Austrian state lender Hypo Alpe Adria loses 1.86 bln euros
-- By Michael Shields
-- Wed Apr 16, 2014 12:24PM EDT
-- None



VIENNA, April 16 (Reuters) - The net loss at nationalised Austrian bank Hypo Alpe Adria [HAABI.UL] swelled to 1.86 billion euros ($2.57 billion) in 2013 from 23 million a year earlier as risk provisions and writedowns leapt to 1.66 billion euros, it said on Wednesday.

Hypo had said last week it expected to report a record net loss of about 1.9 billion euros for 2013 under IFRS accounting rules. [ID:nL6N0N2247]